Program: Outlook
Title: 26/04/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00g47vq
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 27 Apr 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, a man's struggle to come to terms with the deaths of 27 family members and friends after his wedding was the target of a suicide bombing in Jordan in 2005. We hear from one of the last people still practising the dying craft of banknote engraving. And, the couple in Massachusetts in the USA who've renewed their wedding vows on their diamond anniversary, with the help of the care home and hospice staff who look after them. Show less